# Free Tools & Platforms for AI Executive Agent

## Overview
This document lists all the FREE tools and platforms we're using to build the Executive Agent without spending a single dime.

---

## 1. AI/LLM Models & APIs

### OpenAI API (Free Tier)
- **URL**: https://platform.openai.com
- **Free Credit**: $5 free credits (expires after 3 months)
- **Models**: GPT-3.5 Turbo, GPT-4 (limited), Embeddings
- **Use Case**: Main LLM for agent reasoning
- **Rate Limits**: Free tier has limits, perfect for development

### Ollama (Local Models)
- **URL**: https://ollama.ai
- **Cost**: FREE
- **Models**: Llama 2, Mistral, Neural Chat (run locally)
- **Use Case**: Local LLM alternative (no API calls)
- **Advantage**: No rate limits, privacy-first

### HuggingFace Spaces
- **URL**: https://huggingface.co/spaces
- **Cost**: FREE (with limits)
- **Use Case**: Host ML models, inference endpoints
- **Advantage**: Community-driven, multiple model options

---

## 2. Framework & Libraries

### CrewAI
- **URL**: https://github.com/joaomdmoura/crewai
- **Cost**: FREE & Open Source
- **Use Case**: Multi-agent orchestration framework
- **License**: MIT

### LangChain
- **URL**: https://github.com/langchain-ai/langchain
- **Cost**: FREE & Open Source
- **Use Case**: Building LLM chains & integrations
- **License**: MIT

### Autogen (Microsoft)
- **URL**: https://microsoft.github.io/autogen/
- **Cost**: FREE & Open Source
- **Use Case**: Multi-agent conversation framework
- **License**: Apache 2.0

---

## 3. Monitoring & Analytics

### Comet ML (Free Tier)
- **URL**: https://www.comet.com
- **Free Tier**: 50GB storage, team workspaces
- **Use Case**: Experiment tracking, model monitoring
- **Features**: Real-time dashboards, no credit card required

### Opik by Comet (Free)
- **URL**: https://www.opik.ai
- **Cost**: FREE (Open Source)
- **Use Case**: LLM evaluation & testing
- **Features**: Trace LLM calls, measure quality

### W&B (Weights & Biases) - Free Tier
- **URL**: https://wandb.ai
- **Free Tier**: Personal projects, unlimited storage
- **Use Case**: Model training tracking, hyperparameter logging
- **Advantage**: Better UI than Comet for some use cases

---

## 4. Database & Storage

### PostgreSQL (Self-Hosted)
- **URL**: https://www.postgresql.org
- **Cost**: FREE & Open Source
- **Use Case**: Store agent state, conversation history
- **Advantage**: Powerful, free, reliable

### MongoDB Atlas (Free Tier)
- **URL**: https://www.mongodb.com/cloud/atlas
- **Free Tier**: 512MB storage, 3 nodes
- **Use Case**: Document storage for agent memory
- **Advantage**: Cloud-hosted, no setup

### Redis Cloud (Free Tier)
- **URL**: https://redis.com/cloud/
- **Free Tier**: 30MB, 1 database
- **Use Case**: Caching, session management, rate limiting
- **Advantage**: In-memory, fast

### Supabase (Free Tier)
- **URL**: https://supabase.com
- **Free Tier**: PostgreSQL + Auth + Storage
- **Use Case**: Backend database + authentication
- **Advantage**: Open Source, PostgreSQL-based

---

## 5. Browser Automation

### Browser-Use
- **URL**: https://github.com/browser-use/browser-use
- **Cost**: FREE & Open Source
- **Use Case**: Automate browser tasks (our primary tool)
- **Features**: Selenium + AI integration

### Playwright (Free)
- **URL**: https://playwright.dev
- **Cost**: FREE & Open Source
- **Use Case**: Cross-browser automation
- **Advantage**: Modern, fast, supports headless mode

### Selenium
- **URL**: https://www.selenium.dev
- **Cost**: FREE & Open Source
- **Use Case**: Web automation (older but reliable)
- **License**: Apache 2.0

---

## 6. Version Control & CI/CD

### GitHub
- **URL**: https://github.com
- **Cost**: FREE (with limits)
- **Use Case**: Code repository, version control
- **Features**: 2000 CI/CD minutes/month (free)

### GitHub Actions
- **Cost**: FREE (2000 minutes/month)
- **Use Case**: Automated testing, deployment
- **Advantage**: Native to GitHub, no external tools needed

### GitLab CI/CD
- **URL**: https://gitlab.com
- **Cost**: FREE with 10GB storage
- **Use Case**: Alternative to GitHub with generous CI/CD minutes

---

## 7. Cloud Hosting (Free Tier)

### Replit
- **URL**: https://replit.com
- **Free Tier**: 0.5 vCPU, 500MB RAM
- **Use Case**: Host Python agent, quick deployment
- **Advantage**: Browser-based IDE, instant deploy

### Railway (Free Tier)
- **URL**: https://railway.app
- **Free Tier**: $5/month credit (ongoing)
- **Use Case**: Deploy agent services
- **Advantage**: Simple deployment, GitHub integration

### Render
- **URL**: https://render.com
- **Free Tier**: 750 hours/month
- **Use Case**: Host web services, cron jobs
- **Advantage**: Good for long-running agents

### Fly.io
- **URL**: https://fly.io
- **Free Tier**: 3 shared-cpu-1x VMs
- **Use Case**: Global deployment

---

## 8. API & Integration Services

### Make (Formerly Integromat)
- **URL**: https://www.make.com
- **Free Tier**: 1,000 operations/month
- **Use Case**: Connect APIs, webhooks, automations

### Zapier (Free Tier)
- **URL**: https://zapier.com
- **Free Tier**: 100 tasks/month
- **Use Case**: Low-code automation

### n8n (Self-Hosted Free)
- **URL**: https://n8n.io
- **Cost**: FREE & Open Source
- **Use Case**: Workflow automation
- **Advantage**: Self-hosted, unlimited workflows

---

